Write a Prolog program to implement maxlist(L, M) so that M is the maximum number in the list.
Solution 

max(X, Y, M):- X > Y, M is X, !.
max(X, Y, M):- Y >= X, M is Y.
maxlist([H], H):- !.
maxlist([H|T], M):-
 maxlist(T, M1),
 max(H, M1, M).

Output 
| ?- maxlist([4,5,7,8,0,1,2],M).
M = 8
yes
| ?- maxlist([2,15,-7,7,-0,1,-2],M).
M = 15
yes
| ?-
